p: Leaves: A highly diverse set of molecules was found in the essential oil isolated from Z. psammophilum leaves ( Table 1). Methylketones (79.4%) were the main compounds found in this oil; however, sesquiterpenes (14.9%) and diterpenes (2.9%) were also present. The leaf oilâ€™s major components were found to be tridecan-2-one (54.4%), undecan-2-one (20.6%), pentadecan-2-one (4.4%), and tridecan-2-ol (3.8%).
